            "year": 2020,
            "summary": "If not for Ten Thousand compounding factors, each with ten thousand reasons behind them, Bernie Sanders would not be sitting behind the Resolute Desk and looking out to the South Lawn. And yet, He has climbed to the top of the heap to claim the mandate for Revolution in America. The glittering eyes of the crowds as state after state falls under a curtain of blue, the silent curses exchanged in headquarters, stories all culminating to one point: Democratic Socialism is triumphant.<br><br>In the halls of the powerbrokers, a sore silence can be heard. In the homes of Middle America, the fire of reaction has been inflamed once again. The jubilant celebrations of the oppressed, overshadowed by the old world plotting to return. Now in office, he must deliver on his agenda, lest he be puppeteered by the same people he despises or be swept away by the same tide that got him into office.",
